From 55766136b3abcf8aef6c832839779d65b505e02a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Balamurugan Ramar <quic_bramar@quicinc.com>
Date: Thu, 10 Apr 2025 23:26:33 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] mac80211: wifi Fix association with AP_VLAN interface

Post Mode 0 Subsystem Recovery (SSR), DVLAN grouped stations are not
getting associated with MLO AP interface. AP sends AUTH response with
MLD mac address as destination address when AP fails to obtain TX_STA
context using sta_info_get with AP_VLAN interface. And STA expects to
receive AUTH response with LINK mac address.

Fix to obtain TX_STA context from sta_info_get_bss makes AP to send
AUTH response with LINK mac address.

Signed-off-by: Sidhanta Sahu <quic_sidhanta@quicinc.com>
Signed-off-by: Balamurugan Ramar <quic_bramar@quicinc.com>
---
 net/mac80211/tx.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/net/mac80211/tx.c b/net/mac80211/tx.c
index f7855aa..e4ebfd6 100644
--- a/net/mac80211/tx.c
+++ b/net/mac80211/tx.c
@@ -1277,7 +1277,7 @@ ieee80211_tx_prepare(struct ieee80211_sub_if_data *sdata,
 			tx->sta = sta_info_get_bss(sdata, hdr->addr1);
 		}
 		if (!tx->sta && !is_multicast_ether_addr(hdr->addr1)) {
-			tx->sta = sta_info_get(sdata, hdr->addr1);
+			tx->sta = sta_info_get_bss(sdata, hdr->addr1);
 			aggr_check = true;
 		}
 	}
-- 
